{
  "segments": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.68,
      "text": "There isn't actually any advantage using inlining or batching"
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "start": 2.68,
      "end": 5.56,
      "text": "because this UDF is just invoked once."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "start": 5.56,
      "end": 8.44,
      "text": "There's really nothing special about it."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "start": 8.44,
      "end": 10.96,
      "text": "The ones that matter the most is you have things like,"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "start": 10.96,
      "end": 15.18,
      "text": "what we told before, you are passing in some kind of input"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "start": 15.18,
      "end": 18.12,
      "text": "value that you're iterating over in the calling query"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "start": 18.12,
      "end": 20.92,
      "text": "on the outside."
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "start": 20.92,
      "end": 25.28,
      "text": "So I think that when Sam did his analysis,"
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "start": 25.28,
      "end": 28.76,
      "text": "looking for a prop bench, despite Microsoft inventing"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "start": 28.76,
      "end": 30.68,
      "text": "the inlining technique with Freud,"
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "start": 30.68,
      "end": 33.04,
      "text": "they could only inline a small portion of what's"
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "start": 33.04,
      "end": 34.72,
      "text": "in their bench mark of these queries."
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "start": 34.72,
      "end": 37.12,
      "text": "Because a bunch of them just couldn't reason about"
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "start": 37.12,
      "end": 38.28,
      "text": "and wasn't able to handle that."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "start": 38.28,
      "end": 40.12,
      "text": "Or in some cases did it did do it,"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "start": 40.12,
      "end": 42.68,
      "text": "it didn't actually get a performance benefit"
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "start": 42.68,
      "end": 44.84,
      "text": "because it wasn't able to do that decorelation"
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "start": 44.84,
      "end": 45.76,
      "text": "of the sub queries."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "start": 45.76,
      "end": 46.28,
      "text": "Yes?"
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "start": 46.28,
      "end": 47.72,
      "text": "The question to Sam, actually."
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "start": 47.72,
      "end": 51.56,
      "text": "So was it because the if conditions were to complex,"
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "start": 51.56,
      "end": 54.04,
      "text": "or was it that there was some things that it just didn't,"
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "start": 54.04,
      "end": 56.76,
      "text": "like there was the clear set and there was something"
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "start": 56.76,
      "end": 59.0,
      "text": "that was in DC one that didn't know how to apply them"
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "start": 59.0,
      "end": 60.68,
      "text": "to the forum."
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "start": 60.68,
      "end": 62.72,
      "text": "Yeah, so I guess Andy can explain this."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "start": 62.72,
      "end": 66.12,
      "text": "But essentially the problem is that when you get in the"
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "start": 66.12,
      "end": 69.72,
      "text": "end, and then you inline it, you get a very complicated"
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "start": 69.72,
      "end": 72.16,
      "text": "sub query with a bunch of them going."
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "start": 72.16,
      "end": 75.52,
      "text": "And then when you put that into SQL7 optimizer,"
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "start": 75.52,
      "end": 78.08,
      "text": "it's unable to be calling that sub query."
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "start": 78.08,
      "end": 80.8,
      "text": "And then you get that problem."
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "start": 80.8,
      "end": 81.6,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "start": 81.6,
      "end": 82.44,
      "text": "Where is it used?"
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "start": 82.44,
      "end": 85.12,
      "text": "The German way of decoiling sub queries"
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "start": 85.12,
      "end": 86.76,
      "text": "can be called any sub query."
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "start": 86.76,
      "end": 89.04,
      "text": "And you get a really good sub query."
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "start": 89.04,
      "end": 90.84,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "start": 90.84,
      "end": 91.68,
      "text": "We'll cover that."
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "start": 91.68,
      "end": 94.32,
      "text": "We'll cover this in more detail next week as well."
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "start": 94.32,
      "end": 99.68,
      "text": "So this is the table we had in the paper that we just came"
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "start": 99.68,
      "end": 101.4,
      "text": "out two months ago."
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "start": 101.4,
      "end": 102.76,
      "text": "And we compared it against SQL7 Oracle,"
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "start": 102.76,
      "end": 103.76,
      "text": "dot, db, and Postgres."
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "start": 103.76,
      "end": 106.64,
      "text": "So Postgres, again, just can't handle any of these things."
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "start": 106.64,
      "end": 109.0,
      "text": "Because the optimizer is not as sophisticated"
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "start": 109.0,
      "end": 110.24,
      "text": "as the commercial ones."
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "start": 110.24,
      "end": 112.48,
      "text": "Oracle will just ignore."
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "start": 112.48,
      "end": 115.84,
      "text": "But in the case of here, ductyb, well, ductyb got"
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "start": 115.84,
      "end": 117.4,
      "text": "to handle everything."
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "start": 117.4,
      "end": 118.72,
      "text": "How is that the case?"
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "start": 118.72,
      "end": 121.44,
      "text": "Well, because last year, the SAM 721 project with two"
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "start": 121.44,
      "end": 124.28,
      "text": "other master students added support for flattening"
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "start": 124.28,
      "end": 126.4,
      "text": "nested lateral joins so that they can"
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "start": 126.4,
      "end": 129.16,
      "text": "support the inlining and the bashing stuff that we've"
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "start": 129.16,
      "end": 130.36,
      "text": "been talking about."
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "start": 130.36,
      "end": 131.08,
      "text": "Oh, sorry."
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "start": 131.08,
      "end": 134.44,
      "text": "And furthermore, they actually submitted the PR to ductyb"
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "start": 134.44,
      "end": 135.28,
      "text": "that actually got merged."
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "start": 135.28,
      "end": 138.24,
      "text": "When you download ductyb, you're getting SAMs and other 721"
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "start": 138.24,
      "end": 142.44,
      "text": "students code to handle the inlining stuff."
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "start": 142.44,
      "end": 144.0,
      "text": "Well, what about Microsoft, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "start": 144.0,
      "end": 149.92,
      "text": "So inlining, you can see for these select UDS in Proc"
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "start": 149.92,
      "end": 151.72,
      "text": "bench, then the Microsoft benchmark base"
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "start": 151.72,
      "end": 154.88,
      "text": "on their UDS, they can only handle two of them."
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "start": 154.88,
      "end": 156.88,
      "text": "So what's going on?"
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "start": 156.88,
      "end": 160.2,
      "text": "And the issue is that, because, as Samardy said,"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "start": 160.2,
      "end": 162.96,
      "text": "they're not as sophisticated as their approach"
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "start": 162.96,
      "end": 164.2,
      "text": "to decoralating subquers."
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "start": 164.2,
      "end": 166.48,
      "text": "It's not as sophisticated as this German approach"
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "start": 166.48,
      "end": 168.32,
      "text": "which we keep alluding to."
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "start": 168.32,
      "end": 169.6,
      "text": "And instead, they're going to basically"
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "start": 169.6,
      "end": 172.44,
      "text": "have these handwritten rules that allow you"
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "start": 172.44,
      "end": 174.68,
      "text": "to do the rewriting inside the query optimizer"
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "start": 174.68,
      "end": 178.92,
      "text": "for different use cases, but not all of them."
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "start": 178.92,
      "end": 182.32,
      "text": "And this paper came out in 2001."
    },
    {
      "id": 76,
      "start": 182.32,
      "end": 186.8,
      "text": "It's before Freud and these computer-generated monstrosity"
    },
    {
      "id": 77,
      "start": 186.8,
      "end": 190.16,
      "text": "queries that all these lateral joins existed."
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "start": 190.16,
      "end": 193.8,
      "text": "So they didn't, I guess they didn't know."
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "start": 193.8,
      "end": 195.08,
      "text": "These things at the time, they didn't"
    },
    {
      "id": 80,
      "start": 195.08,
      "end": 197.16,
      "text": "try to cover them in their rule base."
    },
    {
      "id": 81,
      "start": 197.16,
      "end": 199.4,
      "text": "And they haven't updated it since then."
    },
    {
      "id": 82,
      "start": 199.4,
      "end": 201.68,
      "text": "So in this case here, Microsoft is simply"
    },
    {
      "id": 83,
      "start": 201.68,
      "end": 203.52,
      "text": "the sequence that we simply can't handle"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
      "start": 203.52,
      "end": 207.16,
      "text": "the monstrosity queries that something like Freud or Op-Fell"
    },
    {
      "id": 85,
      "start": 207.16,
      "end": 209.48,
      "text": "is going to generate."
    },
    {
      "id": 86,
      "start": 209.48,
      "end": 212.56,
      "text": "And so the German approach, which we'll see next week,"
    },
    {
      "id": 87,
      "start": 212.56,
      "end": 219.4,
      "text": "can handle any possible decorrelation for subquers."
    },
    {
      "id": 88,
      "start": 219.4,
      "end": 221.52,
      "text": "Because one, they're going to be able to,"
    },
    {
      "id": 89,
      "start": 221.52,
      "end": 223.68,
      "text": "there's going to be more DAGs instead of trees"
    },
    {
      "id": 90,
      "start": 223.68,
      "end": 226.88,
      "text": "in the query plans because allows them reuse the computation"
    },
    {
      "id": 91,
      "start": 226.88,
      "end": 230.28,
      "text": "for one nested query for another part of a query."
    },
    {
      "id": 92,
      "start": 230.28,
      "end": 232.36,
      "text": "And they're going to introduce these additional constructs"
    },
    {
      "id": 93,
      "start": 232.36,
      "end": 234.68,
      "text": "like an dependent join to keep track of the dependencies"
    },
    {
      "id": 94,
      "start": 234.68,
      "end": 238.84,
      "text": "between two different where clauses from clauses and so forth."
    },
    {
      "id": 95,
      "start": 238.84,
      "end": 241.16,
      "text": "And therefore, they can take any possible subquery combination"
    },
    {
      "id": 96,
      "start": 241.16,
      "end": 243.56,
      "text": "you can think of and throw it at the query optimizer"
    },
    {
      "id": 97,
      "start": 243.56,
      "end": 246.36,
      "text": "and it'll be able to handle this."
    },
    {
      "id": 98,
      "start": 246.36,
      "end": 248.0,
      "text": "Dr. Beacon knew this because they're based off"
    },
    {
      "id": 99,
      "start": 248.0,
      "end": 251.4,
      "text": "of what Umbra did or hyper did."
    },
    {
      "id": 100,
      "start": 251.4,
      "end": 253.44,
      "text": "And then Sam and his team came along and extended"
    },
    {
      "id": 101,
      "start": 253.44,
      "end": 256.88,
      "text": "for the lateral join stuff that we needed."
    },
    {
      "id": 102,
      "start": 256.88,
      "end": 259.0,
      "text": "So that's the preview for next week."
    },
    {
      "id": 103,
      "start": 259.0,
      "end": 264.6,
      "text": "We're going to talk about how this works in hyper."
    },
    {
      "id": 104,
      "start": 264.6,
      "end": 270.0,
      "text": "So the main takeaway going back to this table here,"
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "start": 270.0,
      "end": 271.92,
      "text": "inline is fantastic."
    },
    {
      "id": 106,
      "start": 271.92,
      "end": 273.76,
      "text": "If your database server query optimizer"
    },
    {
      "id": 107,
      "start": 273.76,
      "end": 278.16,
      "text": "can handle the large queries that this thing is going to spit out"
    },
    {
      "id": 108,
      "start": 278.16,
      "end": 278.76,
      "text": "and few can."
    },
    {
      "id": 109,
      "start": 281.64,
      "end": 282.68,
      "text": "OK."
    },
    {
      "id": 110,
      "start": 282.68,
      "end": 286.92,
      "text": "So again, I said this before, but this is a big deal."
    },
    {
      "id": 111,
      "start": 286.92,
      "end": 290.48,
      "text": "If you can get, if your query optimizer can handle the kind"
    },
    {
      "id": 112,
      "start": 290.48,
      "end": 293.32,
      "text": "of things that that app felt or forward is going to generate,"
    },
    {
      "id": 113,
      "start": 293.32,
      "end": 296.08,
      "text": "then you get a huge win for speeding up a UDS"
    },
    {
      "id": 114,
      "start": 296.08,
      "end": 298.52,
      "text": "without making any changes to your application code."
    },
    {
      "id": 115,
      "start": 298.52,
      "end": 303.32,
      "text": "And that rarely happens in the world CS or software."
    },
    {
      "id": 116,
      "start": 303.32,
      "end": 303.92,
      "text": "So that's a big deal."
    },
    {
      "id": 117,
      "start": 303.92,
      "end": 307.16,
      "text": "But again, you need to sort the German style, the Umbra style"
    },
    {
      "id": 118,
      "start": 307.16,
      "end": 308.76,
      "text": "de-coilation."
    },
    {
      "id": 119,
      "start": 309.72,
      "end": 313.32,
      "text": "We talked a little bit about how to compile the machine code."
    },
    {
      "id": 120,
      "start": 313.32,
      "end": 316.6,
      "text": "This is going to help some performance slowdown."
    },
    {
      "id": 121,
      "start": 316.6,
      "end": 318.0,
      "text": "But again, since it's still a little bit"
    },
    {
      "id": 122,
      "start": 318.0,
      "end": 320.56,
      "text": "a black box of the optimizer, it's not"
    },
    {
      "id": 123,
      "start": 320.56,
      "end": 324.24,
      "text": "going to get the best performance."
    },
    {
      "id": 124,
      "start": 324.24,
      "end": 327.32,
      "text": "All right, any questions?"
    },
    {
      "id": 125,
      "start": 327.32,
      "end": 328.08,
      "text": "Yes?"
    },
    {
      "id": 126,
      "start": 328.08,
      "end": 330.48,
      "text": "So this is some time."
    },
    {
      "id": 127,
      "start": 330.48,
      "end": 332.68,
      "text": "Can I ask a question about the code that we looked at"
    },
    {
      "id": 128,
      "start": 332.68,
      "end": 334.68,
      "text": "for the conversion?"
    },
    {
      "id": 129,
      "start": 334.68,
      "end": 335.16,
      "text": "Sure."
    },
    {
      "id": 130,
      "start": 335.16,
      "end": 335.96,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 131,
      "start": 335.96,
      "end": 338.08,
      "text": "I mean, this one?"
    },
    {
      "id": 132,
      "start": 338.08,
      "end": 338.92,
      "text": "Yes?"
    },
    {
      "id": 133,
      "start": 338.92,
      "end": 341.92,
      "text": "No, actually the one that we looked at for this Detroit example."
    },
    {
      "id": 134,
      "start": 341.92,
      "end": 342.76,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "id": 135,
      "start": 347.04,
      "end": 348.8,
      "text": "So they're going back like this?"
    },
    {
      "id": 136,
      "start": 348.8,
      "end": 352.44,
      "text": "I was thinking this might actually not be possible if we have,"
    },
    {
      "id": 137,
      "start": 352.44,
      "end": 355.32,
      "text": "instead of the else clause, right there, the third one."
    },
    {
      "id": 138,
      "start": 355.32,
      "end": 359.32,
      "text": "It would replace that else with a simple if condition."
    },
    {
      "id": 139,
      "start": 359.32,
      "end": 362.36,
      "text": "That just says if at total is less than a million."
    },
    {
      "id": 140,
      "start": 362.36,
      "end": 363.36,
      "text": "I can definitely look here."
    },
    {
      "id": 141,
      "start": 363.36,
      "end": 364.32,
      "text": "Millions."
    },
    {
      "id": 142,
      "start": 364.32,
      "end": 368.16,
      "text": "In that case, if you look at the block over there,"
    },
    {
      "id": 143,
      "start": 368.16,
      "end": 370.08,
      "text": "it says ER2.level."
    },
    {
      "id": 144,
      "start": 370.08,
      "end": 373.16,
      "text": "It won't be able to do ER2.level."
    },
    {
      "id": 145,
      "start": 373.16,
      "end": 375.68,
      "text": "It would need to do ER1 or ER2, depending"
    },
    {
      "id": 146,
      "start": 375.68,
      "end": 377.96,
      "text": "on whether that condition is true."
    },
    {
      "id": 147,
      "start": 377.96,
      "end": 383.76,
      "text": "So it won't easily translate from the left to the right."
    },
    {
      "id": 148,
      "start": 383.76,
      "end": 386.16,
      "text": "So it's statement is, if you have it now inside of this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 149,
      "start": 386.16,
      "end": 388.24,
      "text": "another after nested if clause."
    },
    {
      "id": 150,
      "start": 388.24,
      "end": 389.2,
      "text": "No, not nested."
    },
    {
      "id": 151,
      "start": 389.2,
      "end": 392.48,
      "text": "It could just replace the else with this replace the else."
    },
    {
      "id": 152,
      "start": 392.48,
      "end": 396.4,
      "text": "Oh, so this if ends, then you have another if."
    },
    {
      "id": 153,
      "start": 396.4,
      "end": 398.32,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 154,
      "start": 398.32,
      "end": 403.88,
      "text": "And then in that case, if it's less than a million,"
    },
    {
      "id": 155,
      "start": 403.88,
      "end": 406.24,
      "text": "set it to regular."
    },
